# Asset Conventions

## Folder Structure

```
assets/
├── sprites/
│   ├── heroes/<class>/          # warrior/, ranger/, rogue/, wizard/
│   │   └── <state>/frame_NNN.png   # idle/, walk/, attack/, hurt/, inside/
│   ├── enemies/<type>/          # goblin/, wolf/, skeleton/, skeleton_archer/, etc.
│   │   └── <state>/frame_NNN.png
│   ├── buildings/<type>/        # castle/, warrior_guild/, marketplace/, etc.
│   │   └── <state>.png            # built.png, construction.png, damaged.png
│   └── workers/<type>/          # peasant/, tax_collector/
│       └── <state>/frame_NNN.png
├── audio/
│   ├── sfx/                     # Short sound effects (.wav or .ogg)
│   └── ambient/                 # Ambient loops (.ogg)
├── ui/                          # UI skin assets (9-slice panels, icons, buttons)
└── ATTRIBUTION.md               # Required: license + source for every asset
```

## Naming Rules

- All lowercase, underscores for spaces: `warrior_guild`, `skeleton_archer`
- Frame files: `frame_000.png`, `frame_001.png`, etc. (zero-padded to 3 digits)
- State names match `tools/assets_manifest.json` exactly
- Building types match `config.py` BUILDING_COSTS keys exactly

## Sprite Size Rules

- Heroes: 32x32 base (tile-multiple)
- Enemies: 32x32 base
- Buildings: tile-multiple sizes (e.g., castle = 96x96 = 3 tiles)
- All sprites use nearest-neighbor scaling (no anti-aliasing)

## Licensing (Non-negotiable)

- All assets must be **CC0 or permissive** (compatible with commercial Steam release)
- Every new asset file must have a corresponding entry in `assets/ATTRIBUTION.md`
- Source packs go in `.cursor/human_provided/` with their original license files
- Run `python tools/validate_assets.py --check-attribution` after adding assets

## Fallback Safety

- The game generates procedural placeholder sprites when asset files are missing
- This means missing assets won't crash the game, but they look bad
- Always test visually after adding assets: `python main.py`
